OL,3,CCould the UK look to the Channel
OL,4,CIslands for healthier school dinners?
OL,6,FSchools across the Channel Islands say
OL,7,Fthey are already one step ahead after
OL,8,Fthe UK Government announced plans to
OL,9,Fscrap deep-fried foods from student
OL,10,Fcanteen menus in England.
OL,12,FTheir new rules will also see
OL,13,Funhealthy 'grab-and-go' options like
OL,14,Fpizza and sausage rolls banned, and
OL,15,Fdesserts only served once per week.
OL,17,FHowever, the Channel Islands have been
OL,18,Fleading the way on school meals for
OL,19,Fdecades, as both islands already have
OL,20,Ftheir own policies in place.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/7
