OL,3,CCould the UK look to the Channel
OL,4,CIslands for healthier school dinners?
OL,6,FObesity rates in the Channel Islands
OL,7,Fare currently slightly lower than in
OL,8,FEngland - at 56% and 57% across the
OL,9,FBailiwicks, compared to 66%.
OL,11,FBoth islands' Education Departments
OL,12,Fsay they will continue to monitor
OL,13,Fchanges made in the UK, and adapt
OL,14,Ftheir guidance if necessary.
OL,16,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,17,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,18,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,19,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,20,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,21,Fbelow...
